<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-435-765  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 435 765.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  Sept 19 1990 n1514* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>British Telecom's new audioconferencing bridge uses stored programcontrol. (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   British Telecommunications PLC (product introduction).andO;Product:   British Telecom Elite 10/20 (Bridge device) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionBridges (Connector)TeleconferencingUnited Kingdom.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>BRITISH TELECOM'S NEW AUDIOCONFERENCING BRIDGE USESandM;STORED PROGRAM CONTROLandM;British Telecommunications Plc has brought out a 20-line, &quot;technicallyadvanced&quot; telephone bridge for audioconferencing based on Intel's 80154processor.andP;  The console is similar in design to the Elite 5, BritishTelecom's electronic desktop bridge for controlling five phone lines,released three years ago.andP;  The Elite 10/20 automatically controls the decibellevel on a line, which can vary from -3db to -25db because of the differentphysical distances of the line from the exchange.andP;  Telecom's other bridgesuse hardware rather than a processor to control the gain or noise level.andP;  TheElite 10/20 operates through a desk-top console or can alternatively bedriven from an MS-DOS personal computer.andP;  Up to 240 lines can be controlledby daisy chaining bridges together, although control remains centralised fromone personal computer or console.andP;  Features of the bridge includebroadcast-only and listen-only functions.andP;  The unit can also be programmed inadvance, so that telephone conferences can take place and be recorded,without any participation by the user - a facility aimed at internationalcompanies spread across diverse time zones.andP;  Calls can be made by diallinginto the bridge at a pre-set time, or by the bridge operator dialling meetingparticipants.andP;  The personal computer version of the bridge takes advantage ofthe memory facilities of the computer.andP;  It can store a number ofconfigurations for pre-set meetings, has an autodial directory, and a calllog.andP;  The Elite 10 for 10 lines - console system costs #8,500.andP;  The 20-lineversion costs #15,000.andP;  The Elite 10 personal computer version costs #11,300for the software and hardware, while the 20-line version costs #18,300.andO;</TEXT></DOC>